<exercise checkit-seed="3884" checkit-slug="B2" checkit-title="Sampling Techniques">
  <statement>
      
      
      
      
      
      <p>
          For each of the following, classify the sampling technique described as <em>Simple Random Sample</em>, <em>Stratified Random Sampling</em>, <em>Cluster Sampling</em> or <em>Multi-Stage Sampling</em>.  Be sure to justify your choices.
          <ol>
              <li>To measure approval ratings of the incumbent governor, voters are seperated by income and race, and random people are selected from each group and surveyed.</li>
              <li>To measure student satisfaction, students are randomly selected from the student body and surveyed.</li>
              <li>To test the effects of a new fertilizer on apples, a farmer seperates the apples by species, and randomly selects apples from each species to test.</li>
              <li>To test products for defects, a manufacturer seperates products by types, and randomly selects and tests products from each type.</li>
              <li>To measure the effects of a new heart medication, users of the medication are divided by first letter of last name, some letters are randomnly selected, and a few randomly selected users of the medication in each of those groups are tested.</li>
              <li>To measure the effects of a new heart medication, users of the medication are seperated by physical activity level, and then random users of the medication of each level are selected and tested.</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      
      
      
      
     <p>
          <ol>
              <li>Stratified Random Sample</li>
              <li>Simple Random Sampling</li>
              <li>Stratified Random Sample</li>
              <li>Stratified Random Sample</li>
              <li>Multi-Stage Sampling</li>
              <li>Stratified Random Sample</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
          
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
